This paper deals with the problem of fair allocation, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The algorithm presented in the paper involves assigning items to agents based on their maximin share values, which requires efficient data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of approximate MMS values, which suggests the use of machine learning or optimization techniques (cs.AI, cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the complexity of the algorithm and updating MMS bounds, which falls under the category of computational complexity and algorithms (cs.DM).
